The probability that the bulb from company A exceeds the bulb from company B by at least 15 hours is \(P(D \geq 15)\). Standardizing this, the z-score is \(z = \frac{15 - (-50)}{130} = \frac{65}{130} = 0.5\). The probability \(P(Z \geq 0.5)\) for a standard normal variable \(Z\) is \(1 - P(Z < 0.5)\). Using the standard normal distribution, \(P(Z < 0.5) \approx 0.6915\), so \(P(Z \geq 0.5) \approx 1 - 0.6915 = 0.3085\).

