The given probabilities are \(P(A \cup B) = 0.76\) and \(P(A \cup B') = 0.87\), where \(B'\) is the complement of \(B\).

Using the inclusion-exclusion principle:  
- \(P(A \cup B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cap B) = 0.76\)  
- \(P(A \cup B') = P(A) + P(B') - P(A \cap B') = 0.87\)  

Since \(P(B') = 1 - P(B)\) and \(P(A \cap B') = P(A) - P(A \cap B)\), substitute into the second equation:  
\[P(A) + (1 - P(B)) - (P(A) - P(A \cap B)) = 0.87\]  
