- For bowl \(B_2\): \(P(B_2) = \frac{1}{4}\) and \(P(W \mid B_2) = 0\) (since both chips are red), so the contribution is \(0 \times \frac{1}{4} = 0\).
- For bowl \(B_3\): \(P(B_3) = \frac{1}{8}\) and \(P(W \mid B_3) = \frac{2}{4} = 0.5\) (since there are two white and two red chips), so the contribution is \(0.5 \times \frac{1}{8} = 0.0625\).
