The energy required to compress three carbon-carbon single bonds and stretch three carbon-carbon double bonds to the benzene bond length of 1.397 Å is calculated using the harmonic oscillator potential energy formula \( E = \frac{1}{2} k (x - x_0)^2 \), where \( k \) is the force constant, \( x \) is the benzene bond length, and \( x_0 \) is the typical bond length.

For the single bonds:  
- Typical length \( x_0 = 1.53 \, \text{Å} \), force constant \( k = 500 \, \text{N/m} \)  
- Change in length \( \Delta x = 1.397 - 1.53 = -0.133 \, \text{Å} \) (compression)  
- Energy per bond: \( E_{\text{single}} = \frac{1}{2} \times 500 \times (-0.133 \times 10^{-10})^2 \)  
- Convert to consistent units: \( \Delta x = -0.133 \times 10^{-10} \, \text{m} \), so \( (\Delta x)^2 = 1.7689 \times 10^{-22} \, \text{m}^2 \)  
- \( E_{\text{single}} = \frac{1}{2} \times 500 \times 1.7689 \times 10^{-22} = 4.42225 \times 10^{-20} \, \text{J} \)  
- For three bonds: \( 3 \times 4.42225 \times 10^{-20} = 1.326675 \times 10^{-19} \, \text{J} \)  

For the double bonds:  
- Typical length \( x_0 = 1.335 \, \text{Å} \), force constant \( k = 950 \, \text{N/m} \)  
- Change in length \( \Delta x = 1.397 - 1.335 = 0.062 \, \text{Å} \) (stretching)  
- Energy per bond: \( E_{\text{double}} = \frac{1}{2} \times 950 \times (0.062 \times 10^{-10})^2 \)  
- Convert to consistent units: \( \Delta x = 0.062 \times 10^{-10} \, \text{m} \), so \( (\Delta x)^2 = 3.844 \times 10^{-23} \, \text{m}^2 \)  
- \( E_{\text{double}} = \frac{1}{2} \times 950 \times 3.844 \times 10^{-23} = 1.8259 \times 10^{-20} \, \text{J} \)  
- For three bonds: \( 3 \times 1.8259 \times 10^{-20} = 5.4777 \times 10^{-20} \, \text{J} \)  

Total energy for the system:  
- \( E_{\text{total}} = 1.326675 \times 10^{-19} + 5.4777 \times 10^{-20} = 1.874445 \times 10^{-19} \, \text{J} \)  

Convert to per mole:  
- Avogadro's number \( N_A = 6.022 \times 10^{23} \, \text{mol}^{-1} \)  
- \( E_{\text{mol}} = 1.874445 \times 10^{-19} \times 6.022 \times 10^{23} = 1.128790779 \times 10^{5} \, \text{J/mol} \)  

Convert to kcal/mol:  
- \( 1 \, \text{kcal} = 4184 \, \text{J} \)  
- \( E_{\text{kcal/mol}} = \frac{1.128790779 \times 10^{5}}{4184} = 26.978747 \, \text{kcal/mol} \)  

