 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The lifespans of light bulbs from company A and company B are normally distributed and independent. Let \(X\) be the lifespan from company A, \(X \sim N(800, 14400)\), and \(Y\) be the lifespan from company B, \(Y \sim N(850, 2500)\). The difference \(D = X - Y\) follows a normal distribution with mean \(\mu_D = \mu_X - \mu_Y = 800 - 850 = -50\) and variance \(\sigma_D^2 = \sigma_X^2 + \sigma_Y^2 = 14400 + 2500 = 16900\), so standard deviation \(\sigma_D = \sqrt{16900} = 130\).

