- Of those with an irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure, so the percentage with both high blood pressure and irregular heartbeat is \(0.17 \times 0.35 = 0.0595\), or 5.95%.
- 65% of patients have normal blood pressure (since 100% - 16% high - 19% low = 65% normal).
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have an irregular heartbeat, so the percentage with both normal blood pressure and irregular heartbeat is \(0.65 \times 0.11 = 0.0715\), or 7.15%.
- The total with irregular heartbeat is the sum of those with irregular heartbeat and high, normal, or low blood pressure. Thus, the percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure is \(17\% - 5.95\% - 7.15\% = 3.90\%\).
- 19% of patients have low blood pressure, which includes both regular and irregular heartbeats. Therefore, the percentage with low blood pressure and regular heartbeat is \(19\% - 3.90\% = 15.10\%\).

Rounding 15.10% to one decimal place gives 15.1%, as the inputs and calculations support a reasonable precision of one decimal.

